						<div class="postbody">Some games don't do any sprite DMA at all for several frames on end, such as Metal Max when a text box is displayed.<br />Other games do a second sprite DMA in the middle of the screen.<br />RC Pro Am (PRG0) does weird things with sprites: It DMAs a bunch of FF bytes from ROM, then manually writes a few sprites with OAM writes.  This happens during rendering time with the screen turned off.  The game also does a normal sprite DMA during vblank time.</div>

					
